<plot>A film about the unusual friendship that has been shared by six men for some 35 years since Vietnam. This documentary explores their Navy service in the Mekong Delta, the effect the war had on them, how their experience in Vietnam became the basis of a friendship, and what it is that constitutes their "unbreakable bond." The group decides to visit the Vietnam Veterans Memorial Wall in Washington, D.C.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?084467</url></doc>
